<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="67" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,586,1212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<number box="[151,167,586,612]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="1.0">1</number>
. Smaller, length (labrum to elytral apex) usually less than 0.59 mm; pronotum less transverse, sides more rounded, posterior angles little defined (
<figureCitation box="[679,752,626,652]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1185,1209]" captionTargetBox="[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Scanning electron micrographs of Ptiliola flammifera (1, 4, 5), P. kunzei (2, 6) and P. brevicollis (3). 1 – 3. Pronotum, scale bar 50 μm; 4. Male metaventrite, scale bar 20 μm; 5, 6. Apical fringe of elytra, scale bar 10 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178001/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[736,752,626,652]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Male: aedeagal sclerites not reaching half the length of the aedeagus, strongly sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[610,738,666,692]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[308,1285,1225,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[295,1292,1214,1670]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Aedeagi of Ptiliola flammifera (7, 10), P. kunzei (8, 11) and P. brevicollis (9, 12) in ventral (7 – 9) and lateral (10 – 12) view. Scale bar 50 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178002/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Figs. 
<number box="[676,738,666,692]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="9.12">9, 12</number>
</figureCitation>
); metaventrite simple 
<emphasis box="[996,1291,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Matthews" authorityName="Matthews" box="[1140,1291,666,691]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiliidae" genus="Ptiliola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicollis">P. brevicollis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(Matthews)
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,586,1212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
- Larger, length usually more than 0.59 mm; pronotum more transverse, sides less rounded, somewhat narrowed anteriad (
<figureCitation box="[396,516,746,772]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1185,1209]" captionTargetBox="[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Scanning electron micrographs of Ptiliola flammifera (1, 4, 5), P. kunzei (2, 6) and P. brevicollis (3). 1 – 3. Pronotum, scale bar 50 μm; 4. Male metaventrite, scale bar 20 μm; 5, 6. Apical fringe of elytra, scale bar 10 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178001/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Figs. 
<number box="[465,516,746,772]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="1.2">1, 2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Male: aedeagal sclerites larger, more than half the length of the aedeagus, sclerotization weaker (
<figureCitation box="[464,664,786,812]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[308,1285,1225,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[295,1292,1214,1670]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Aedeagi of Ptiliola flammifera (7, 10), P. kunzei (8, 11) and P. brevicollis (9, 12) in ventral (7 – 9) and lateral (10 – 12) view. Scale bar 50 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178002/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Figs. 
<number box="[531,576,786,812]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="7.8">7, 8</number>
, 
<number box="[589,664,786,812]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="10.11">10, 11</number>
</figureCitation>
); metaventrite simple or ornated with a tuft of hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1285,1356,786,812]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1185,1209]" captionTargetBox="[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Scanning electron micrographs of Ptiliola flammifera (1, 4, 5), P. kunzei (2, 6) and P. brevicollis (3). 1 – 3. Pronotum, scale bar 50 μm; 4. Male metaventrite, scale bar 20 μm; 5, 6. Apical fringe of elytra, scale bar 10 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178001/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[1340,1356,786,812]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) ...... 
<number box="[1419,1434,786,812]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2.0">2</number>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,586,1212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<number box="[151,169,826,852]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2.0">2</number>
. Apical fringe of elytra regular and somewhat wider (
<figureCitation box="[812,882,826,852]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1185,1209]" captionTargetBox="[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Scanning electron micrographs of Ptiliola flammifera (1, 4, 5), P. kunzei (2, 6) and P. brevicollis (3). 1 – 3. Pronotum, scale bar 50 μm; 4. Male metaventrite, scale bar 20 μm; 5, 6. Apical fringe of elytra, scale bar 10 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178001/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[867,882,826,852]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) (this character is best appreciated by transmitted light microscopy). Pronotal reticulation somewhat coarser and less pronounced, especially towards the frontal margin (
<figureCitation box="[384,453,906,932]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1185,1209]" captionTargetBox="[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Scanning electron micrographs of Ptiliola flammifera (1, 4, 5), P. kunzei (2, 6) and P. brevicollis (3). 1 – 3. Pronotum, scale bar 50 μm; 4. Male metaventrite, scale bar 20 μm; 5, 6. Apical fringe of elytra, scale bar 10 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178001/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[439,453,906,932]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); as a result the overall appearance of the pronotum, when studied under reflecting light, more shiny. Male: aedeagus smaller; aedeagal sclerites in ventral view more stout (
<figureCitation box="[1233,1303,946,972]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[308,1285,1225,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[295,1292,1214,1670]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Aedeagi of Ptiliola flammifera (7, 10), P. kunzei (8, 11) and P. brevicollis (9, 12) in ventral (7 – 9) and lateral (10 – 12) view. Scale bar 50 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178002/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[1287,1303,946,972]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
); metaventrite smoothly excavated, apically bordered by a distinct tuft of erect hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1079,1150,986,1012]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1185,1209]" captionTargetBox="[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Scanning electron micrographs of Ptiliola flammifera (1, 4, 5), P. kunzei (2, 6) and P. brevicollis (3). 1 – 3. Pronotum, scale bar 50 μm; 4. Male metaventrite, scale bar 20 μm; 5, 6. Apical fringe of elytra, scale bar 10 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178001/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[1134,1150,986,1012]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) .................................... 
<emphasis box="[204,1287,1026,1051]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
.............................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Mlynarski" authorityName="Mlynarski" box="[1125,1287,1026,1051]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiliidae" genus="Ptiliola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flammifera">P. flammifera</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(Młynarski)
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,586,1212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
- Apical fringe of elytra more narrow, towards the suture fused to form a few brush-shaped extensions (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1185,1209]" captionTargetBox="[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Scanning electron micrographs of Ptiliola flammifera (1, 4, 5), P. kunzei (2, 6) and P. brevicollis (3). 1 – 3. Pronotum, scale bar 50 μm; 4. Male metaventrite, scale bar 20 μm; 5, 6. Apical fringe of elytra, scale bar 10 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178001/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[199,216,1106,1132]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotal reticulation somewhat finer and more pronounced (
<figureCitation box="[950,1022,1106,1132]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1185,1209]" captionTargetBox="[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[277,1310,197,1159]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Scanning electron micrographs of Ptiliola flammifera (1, 4, 5), P. kunzei (2, 6) and P. brevicollis (3). 1 – 3. Pronotum, scale bar 50 μm; 4. Male metaventrite, scale bar 20 μm; 5, 6. Apical fringe of elytra, scale bar 10 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178001/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[1005,1022,1106,1132]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); as a result the overall appearance more dull. Male: aedeagus larger; aedeagal sclerites in ventral view more slender, somewhat contracted in the middle (
<figureCitation box="[339,411,1186,1212]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[308,1285,1225,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[295,1292,1214,1670]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Aedeagi of Ptiliola flammifera (7, 10), P. kunzei (8, 11) and P. brevicollis (9, 12) in ventral (7 – 9) and lateral (10 – 12) view. Scale bar 50 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178002/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[394,411,1186,1212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
); metaventrite simple 
<emphasis box="[666,1349,1187,1212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
............................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Heer" authorityName="Heer" box="[1247,1349,1187,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Trichopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kunzei">P. kunzei</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(Heer)
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
